snippet: The U.S. services industry slowed in September but still showed growth, while another report said private-sector employers added 91,000 jobs, reports showed Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: The U.S. services industry slowed in September but still showed growth, while another report said private-sector employers added 91,000 jobs, reports showed Wednesday.

headline.main: Services Sector Inches Ahead, Report Says
